The paper discusses the ethical and social problems arising from the use of ICT, and proposes a large-scale EU flagship proposal called FuturICT to address these issues. The paper also discusses the institutional design of FuturICT. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.CS (Computer Science), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper also discusses the use of ICT-based research and the complexity of modern societies.
